ALGORITHM:
Aim: To demonstrate tuple operations and related functions in Python.

Steps

Start the program.

Create a tuple student = ("Yukthi", 19, "CSE", "Python", "Java", "Python").

Display the length of the tuple using len().

Create another tuple **student2 = ("Meera", 20, "CSI", "Java", "C")`.

Join both tuples using the concatenation operator + and store the result in t.

Display the final joined tuple.

Count the occurrence of "Meera" in the second tuple using count() and display it.

Display the length of the first tuple using len().

Display the length of the second tuple using len().

Display the first three elements of the first tuple using slicing [0:3].

Display the last element of the second tuple using negative indexing [-1].

Stop the program.

